%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20chart%20shows%20the%20most%20common%20symptoms%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20people%20under%2050%2C%20as%20cases%20in%20younger%20people%20rise%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20holding%20her%20stomach%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6655e146239fda2da6cbfb41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERectal%20bleeding%20and%20abdominal%20pain%20were%20the%20most%20common%20signs%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20younger%20people%20in%20a%20study.%3Cp%3ELaylaBird%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20most%20common%20symptom%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20younger%20adults%20is%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20a%20study%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERates%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20people%20under%2055%20have%20risen%20significantly%20since%20the%20mid-1990s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20identified%2017%20symptoms%20that%20patients%20and%20doctors%20should%20look%20out%20for.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERectal%20bleeding%2C%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20and%20changes%20in%20bowel%20habits%20were%20identified%20as%20the%20most%20common%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorectal-cancer-high-mortality-young-people-signs-symptoms-disease-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20younger%20adults%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20new%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disease%20is%20affecting%20more%20and%20more%20younger%20adults%2C%20as%20rates%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20people%20under%2055%20have%20risen%20significantly%20since%20the%20mid-1990s.%20Between%202011%20and%202019%2C%20rates%20increased%20by%201.9%25%20a%20year%20in%20people%20younger%20than%2055%2C%20according%20to%20existing%20research%20by%20The%20American%20Cancer%20Society.%20Although%20cases%20rose%20in%20all%20age%20groups%20under%2050%20during%20this%20period%2C%20the%20biggest%20uptick%20was%20seen%20in%20people%20in%20their%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-cases-doubled-young-people-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20late%2020s%20to%20early%2030s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20rate%20of%20colon%20cancer%20for%20people%20in%20that%20age%20group%20increased%20by%20about%2070%25%20from%201999%20to%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20data.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20weight%20loss%20and%20appetite%20changes%2C%20can%20be%20indicative%20of%20many%20illnesses%2C%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20news%20study%20published%20May%2024%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2819248%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJAMA%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote.%20This%20means%20they're%20often%20missed%2C%20leading%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fignored-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-abdominal-pain-bloody-stool-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elate-stage%20diagnosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20harder%20to%20treat%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20combat%20this%2C%20researchers%20used%20data%20from%2081%20studies%20across%20six%20countries%20involving%20nearly%2025%20million%20people%20under%2050%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-red-flag-signs-symptoms-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly-onset%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20aim%20was%20to%20determine%20which%20symptoms%20were%20most%20common%2C%20which%20signs%20put%20patients%20most%20at%20risk%20of%20colon%20cancer%2C%20and%20how%20long%20it%20took%20patients%20to%20get%20a%20colon%20cancer%20diagnosis.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%2017%20signs%20of%20early-onset%20colon%20cancer%20were%20identified.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3hOEB%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%2017%20signs%20of%20early-onset%20colon%20cancer%20identified%20in%20the%20study%5Cn%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22758%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20the%20participants%20had%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20which%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20five-fold%20increase%20in%20early%20onset%20colon%20cancer%20risk%2C%20making%20it%20the%20largest%20risk%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2040%25%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-women-whose-abdominal-pain-and-other-symptoms-were-dismissed-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabdominal%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20second%20most%20common%20symptom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20bowel%20movements%20was%20the%20third%2C%20and%20included%20constipation%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20alternating%20bowel%20habits%2C%20or%20alternating%20diarrhea%20or%20constipation.%20The%20fourth%20most%20common%20symptom%20in%20the%20US%20was%20diarrhea%2C%20but%20in%20studies%20from%20non-US%20countries%2C%20it%20was%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20tended%20to%20receive%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%20between%20four%20to%20six%20months%20after%20their%20symptoms%20first%20appeared.%20It's%20not%20clear%20whether%20decreasing%20the%20time%20to%20diagnosis%20would%20improve%20outcomes%2C%20but%20the%20risk%20of%20cancer%20becoming%20advanced%20increases%20over%20time%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20suggested%20that%20given%20the%20prevalence%20of%20rectal%20bleeding%20and%20abdominal%20pain%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-colonoscopy-colon-cancer-symptoms-colorectal-oncologist-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20doctors%20should%20always%20consider%20it%20before%20dismissing%20a%20patient%20with%20these%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20significant%20differences%20in%20the%20studies%20used%2C%20which%20posed%20some%20challenges%20for%20analysis%2C%20the%20authors%20said.%20They%20were%20unable%20to%20compare%20colon%20cancer%20risk%20against%20other%20potential%20causes%20of%20symptoms%2C%20which%20might%20have%20provided%20a%20better%20picture%20of%20the%20relative%20risk%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20still%20don't%20know%20what's%20behind%20the%20rise%20in%20colon%20cancer%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-health-problems-study-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20environmental%20contaminants%2C%20and%20obesity%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20are%20being%20considered%20possible%20causes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-symptoms-colon-cancer-under-50s-chart-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716980132000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6655e168239fda2da6cbfb4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-symptoms-colon-cancer-under-50s-chart-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Colon%20cancer%20is%20affecting%20more%20younger%20adults%2C%20but%20it's%20easy%20to%20dismiss%20symptoms%20when%20they%20have%20similarities%20with%20less%20severe%20diseases.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40businessinsider.com%20(Kim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-symptoms-colon-cancer-under-50s-chart-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20Hits%2052.3%20Degrees%2C%20Highest-Ever%20Recorded%20Temperature%20In%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20weather%20office%20in%20Delhi%20has%20recorded%20the%20highest-ever%20temperature%20the%20country%20has%20experienced%20at%2052.3%20degree%20Celsius%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20capital%20also%20reported%20its%20all-time%20high%20power%20demand%20of%208%2C302%20megawatts%20(MW)%20amid%20the%20heatwave%20as%20more%20and%20more%20residents%20turned%20on%20power-intensive%20air-conditioning%2C%20electricity%20department%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20areas%20that%20reported%20extremely%20high%20temperature%20are%20both%20in%20the%20desert%20state%20Rajasthan%20-%2051%20degree%20Celsius%20in%20Phalodi%2C%20and%2050.8%20degree%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESirsa%20in%20Haryana%20recorded%2050.3%20degree%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fall%20of%20up%20to%204%20degree%20Celsius%20over%20south%20Rajasthan%20districts%20-%20Barmer%2C%20Jodhpur%2C%20Udaipur%2C%20Sirohi%2C%20and%20Jalore%20-%20has%20been%20recorded%20today%20due%20to%20moist%20wind%20incursion%20from%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%2C%20indicating%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20heatwave%20reduction%20over%20northwest%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716979800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fkcpn93t8_delhi-heat_625x300_29_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-hits-52-3-degrees-highest-ever-recorded-temperature-5771382%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20weather%20office%20in%20Delhi%20has%20recorded%20the%20highest-ever%20temperature%20the%20country%20has%20experienced%20at%2052.3%20degree%20Celsius%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-hits-52-3-degrees-highest-ever-recorded-temperature-5771382%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-hits-52-3-degrees-highest-ever-recorded-temperature-5771382%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-hits-52-3-degrees-highest-ever-recorded-temperature-5771382%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fire%20Officer%2C%20Town%20Planning%20Officer%20Detained%20in%20Rajkot%20Gaming%20Zone%20Tragedy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20major%20action%20in%20the%20Rajkot%20gaming%20zone%20fire%20that%20killed%2027%20people%2C%20including%20nine%20children%2C%20the%20police%20have%20detained%20a%20fire%20officer%20and%20the%20town%20planning%20officer%20for%20questioning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETown%20Planning%20Officer%20MD%20Sagathia%20and%20Fire%20Officer%20BJ%20Theba%2C%20both%20from%20the%20Rajkot%20Municipal%20Corporation%2C%20were%20detained%20by%20the%20Rajkot%20Crime%20Branch%20on%20Wednesday%20afternoon.%20The%20officials%20are%20being%20interrogated%20and%20the%20key%20questions%20that%20will%20be%20asked%20of%20them%20are%20how%20the%20TRP%20Gaming%20Zone%2C%20where%20the%20tragedy%20occurred%20on%20Saturday%2C%20was%20operating%20only%20with%20an%20entertainment%20licence%20and%20without%20a%20no-objection%20certificate%2C%20an%20approved%20layout%20plan%2C%20building-use%20certificate%20and%20the%20proper%20fire%20clearances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20owners%20of%20the%20establishment%20-%20Yuvrajsinh%20Solanki%2C%20Rahul%20Rathod%2C%20Dhaval%20Thakkar%20and%20Kiritsinh%20Jadeja%20-%20are%20among%20five%20people%20who%20have%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20case%20and%20a%20fifth%20-%20Prakash%20Hiran%20-%20perished%20in%20the%20fire%2C%20a%20DNA%20test%20had%20revealed%20on%20Tuesday.%20The%20manager%2C%20Nitin%20Jain%2C%20is%20also%20in%20police%20custody.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20have%20been%20charged%20under%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20Sections%20304%20(culpable%20homicide)%2C%20308%20(attempt%20to%20commit%20culpable%20homicide)%2C%20337%20(causing%20hurt%20by%20an%20act%20that%20endangers%20the%20life%20or%20personal%20safety%20of%20others)%2C%20338%20(causing%20grievous%20hurt%20to%20a%20person%20by%20doing%20an%20act%20that%20endangers%20their%20life%20or%20