SK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Three%20Israeli%20soldiers%20killed%20in%20combat%20in%20southern%20Gaza%2C%20military%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716975914000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110532628%2Cimgsize-13220.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fthree-israeli-soldiers-killed-in-combat-in-southern-gaza-military-says%2Farticleshow%2F110532643.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F110532643.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThree%20Israeli%20soldiers%20killed%20in%20combat%20in%20southern%20Gaza%20in%20the%20ongoing%20offensive%20in%20Rafah%2C%20sparking%20outrage%20over%20civilian%20casualties%20and%20displacement%20of%20Palestinian%20civilians%20by%20the%20Israeli%20military.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fthree-israeli-soldiers-killed-in-combat-in-southern-gaza-military-says%2Farticleshow%2F110532643.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fthree-israeli-soldiers-killed-in-combat-in-southern-gaza-military-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F110532643.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fthree-israeli-soldiers-killed-in-combat-in-southern-gaza-military-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F110532643.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20What%20Probe%20Into%20Turbulence-Hit%20Singapore%20Airlines%20Flight%20Reveals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Singapore%20Airlines%20Flight%20SQ321%2C%20en%20route%20from%20London%20to%20Singapore%2C%20was%20dramatically%20disrupted%20by%20severe%20turbulence%20while%20cruising%20at%2037%2C000%20feet%20over%20Myanmar.%20Preliminary%20findings%20released%20by%20Singapore's%20Transport%20Safety%20Investigation%20Bureau%20(TSIB)%20provide%20a%20detailed%20account%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20revealing%20the%20violent%20nature%20of%20the%20turbulence%20and%20its%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2021%2C%20Flight%20SQ321%2C%20a%20Boeing%20777-300ER%20carrying%20211%20passengers%20and%2018%20crew%20members%2C%20encountered%20unexpected%20and%20extreme%20turbulence.%20This%20sudden%20turbulence%20resulted%20in%20one%20death%2C%20with%20a%20passenger%20suspected%20of%20suffering%20a%20heart%20attack%2C%20and%20numerous%20injuries%20among%20those%20on%20board.%20The%20flight%20was%20forced%20to%20make%20an%20emergency%20landing%20in%20Thailand's%20capital%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20aircraft%20experienced%20a%20rapid%20change%20in%20G%20(gravitational%20force).%20This%20likely%20resulted%20in%20the%20occupants%20who%20were%20not%20belted%20up%20to%20become%20airborne%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Singapore%20transport%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20citing%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Transport%20Safety%20Investigation%20Bureau%20of%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20TSIB%20findings%2C%20Flight%20SQ321%20departed%20from%20London%20on%20May%2020%20and%20maintained%20a%20normal%20flight%20path%20until%20the%20turbulence%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20revealed%20that%20the%20gravitational%20force%20(G-force)%20fluctuated%20between%20%2B0.44G%20and%20%2B1.57G%20over%2019%20seconds%2C%20causing%20initial%20vibrations.%20The%20aircraft%20experienced%20an%20uncommanded%20altitude%20increase%20to%2037%2C362%20feet%2C%20likely%20due%20to%20an%20updraft.%20The%20autopilot%20attempted%20to%20correct%20this%20by%20pitching%20the%20aircraft%20down%2C%20and%20the%20pilots%20managed%20an%20uncommanded%20airspeed%20increase%20by%20extending%20the%20speed%20brakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vertical%20acceleration%20changed%20from%20negative%201.5G%20to%20positive%201.5G%20within%204%20seconds.%20This%20likely%20resulted%20in%20the%20occupants%20who%20were%20airborne%20to%20fall%20back%20down.%20The%20rapid%20changes%20in%20G%20over%20the%204.6%20seconds%20duration%20resulted%20in%20an%20altitude%20drop%20of%20178%20ft%20(54%20m)%2C%20from%2037%2C362%20ft%20to%2037%2C184%20ft.%20This%20sequence%20of%20events%20likely%20caused%20the%20injuries%20to%20the%20crew%20and%20passengers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20The%20Crew%20Responded%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20turbulence%2C%20the%20pilots%20disengaged%20the%20autopilot%20and%20manually%20controlled%20the%20aircraft%20for%2021%20seconds%20to%20stabilise%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20re-engaged%20the%20autopilot%20at%2007%3A50%3A05%20UTC%20and%20the%20aircraft%20returned%20to%20its%20cruising%20altitude%20of%2037%2C000%20feet%20by%2007%3A50%3A23%20UTC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20assessing%20the%20injuries%20and%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20the%20pilots%20diverted%20the%20plane%20to%20Suvarnabhumi%20Airport%20in%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20coordinated%20with%20air%20traffic%20control%20to%20ensure%20medical%20services%20were%20ready%20upon%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20began%20a%20controlled%20descent%20at%2008%3A06%20UTC%20and%20landed%20safely%20at%2008%3A45%20UTC%20without%20encountering%20further%20severe%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20violent%20turbulence%20resulted%20in%20several%20injuries%20among%20passengers%20and%20crew%20members.%20The%20sudden%20shifts%20in%20G-force%20and%20altitude%20threw%20unsecured%20individuals%20against%20the%20cabin%20structure%2C%20causing%20severe%20trauma.%20Tragically%2C%20one%20passenger%20suffered%20a%20suspected%20heart%20attack%20and%20could%20not%20be%20revived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TSIB%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20(NTSB)%2C%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20(FAA)%2C%20and%20Boeing%2C%20continues%20to%20investigate%20the%20incident.%20Data%20from%20the%20flight%20data%20recorder%20(FDR)%20and%20cockpit%20voice%20recorder%20(CVR)%20have%20been%20analysed%20to%20compile%20a%20detailed%20chronology%20of%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20committed%20to%20supporting%20our%20passengers%20and%20crew%20members%20who%20were%20on%20board%20SQ321%20on%20that%20day%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20families%20and%20loved%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20Singapore%20Airlines%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716975900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fb67hm7d_singapore-airlines_625x300_22_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-probe-into-turbulence-hit-singapore-airlines-flight-reveals-5770983%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Last%20week%2C%20Singapore%20Airlines%20Flight%20SQ321%2C%20en%20route%20from%20London%20to%20Singapore%2C%20was%20dramatically%20disrupted%20by%20severe%20turbulence%20while%20cruising%20at%2037%2C000%20feet%20over%20Myanmar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-probe-into-turbulence-hit-singapore-airlines-flight-reveals-5770983%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-probe-into-turbulence-hit-singapore-airlines-flight-reveals-5770983%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-what-probe-into-turbulence-hit-singapore-airlines-flight-reveals-5770983%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20Scientists%20Unveil%20Potential%20Diabetes%20Cure%20With%20New%20Cell%20Therapy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20promising%20development%20for%20millions%20with%20diabetes%2C%20researchers%20in%20China%20have%20reported%20a%20potential%20cure%20using%20cell%20therapy.%20The%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Cell%20Discovery%2C%20details%20the%20successful%20treatment%20of%20a%2059-year-old%20man%20with%20type%202%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20patient%2C%20who%20had%20been%20battling%20the%20disease%20for%2025%20years%20and%20relied%20on%20daily%20insulin%20injections%2C%20underwent%20an%20innovative%20cell%20transplant%20in%20July%202021.%20The%20procedure%20involved%20creating%20lab-grown%20replicas%20of%20insulin-producing%20islet%20cells%2C%20found%20in%20the%20pancreas%2C%20which%20were%20then%20transplanted%20into%20the%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fscience%2Farticle%2F3263878%2Fchinese-scientists-report-world-first-they-cure-patients-diabetes-cell-therapy%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESouth%20China%20Morning%20Post%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20treatment%20proved%20remarkably%20successful.%20Within%20eleven%20weeks%2C%20the%20patient%20no%20longer%20required%20external%20insulin.%20Over%20the%20following%20year%2C%20he%20gradually%20reduced%20and%20eventually%20stopped%20taking%20oral%20medication%20for%20blood%20sugar%20control.%20Follow-up%20examinations%20confirmed%20a%20restored%20function%20in%20the%20patient's%20pancreatic%20islet%20cells%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20remain%20medication-free%20for%20over%2033%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20a%20single-patient%20case%20study%2C%20experts%20view%20it%20as%20a%20significant%20breakthrough%20in%20cell%20therapy%20for%20diabetes.%20Professor%20Timothy%20Kieffer%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Ban%20important%20advance%20in%20the%20field.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20further%20large-scale%20trials%20are%20needed%20to%20confirm%20the%20efficacy%20and%20safety%20of%20this%20approach%20before%20it%20can%20be%20widely%20used%20as%20a%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20news%20brings%20hope%20to%20millions%20of%20people%20with%20diabetes.%20More%20research%20is%20needed%2C%20but%20this%20successful%20cell%20therapy%20trial%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20future%20without%20the%20disease.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EDiabetes%20around%20the%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidf.org%2Fabout-diabetes%2Fdiabetes-facts-figures%2F%5C%22%3EInternational%20Diabetes%20Federation%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IDF)%20paints%20a%20concerning%20picture%3A%20By%202021%2C%20an%20estimated%20537%20million%20adults%20aged%2020-79%20already%20had%20diabetes.%20This%20number%20is%20projected%20to%20explode%2C%20reaching%20643%20million%20by%202030%20and%20a%20staggering%20783%20million%20by%202045.%20This%20translates%20to%201%20in%208%20adults%20globally%20projected%20to%20have%20diabetes%20by%202045%2C%20a%2046%25%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20alarming%20is%20the%20unequal%20distribution%20of%20this%20burden.%20A%20staggering%203%20out%20of%204%20adults%20with%20diabetes%20live%20in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20These%20statistics%20highlight%20the%20growing%20global%20challenge%20of%20diabetes%20and%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20effective%20prevention%20and%20management%20strategies%2C%20particularly%20focused%20on%20supporting%20developing%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716975900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Ftdi9jn88_healthy-foods-to-eat-in-diabetes_625x300_01_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchinese-scientists-reveal-potential-diabetes-cure-with-innovative-cell-therapy-5770913%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20treatment%20proved%20remarkably%20successful.%20Within%20eleven%20weeks%2C%20the%20patient%20no%20longer%20re