C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fprestige-estates-q4-result-profit-falls-70-to-rs-140-cr-on-lower-income-124052900762_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Denmark%20has%20the%20solution%20to%20America's%20broken%20housing%20market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22House%20with%20Danish%20flag%20flying%20in%20the%20sunlight%2C%20while%20next%20door%2C%20a%20house%20with%20an%20American%20flag%20is%20being%20rained%20on%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66561a93239fda2da6cc30ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMillions%20of%20Americans%20are%20trapped%20in%20their%20homes%20thanks%20to%20rising%20mortgage%20rates.%20But%20a%20genius%20rule%20lets%20Danish%20homeowners%20dodge%20the%20lock-in%20effect.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typical%20home%20loan%20in%20America%20is%20a%20gift.%20It's%20also%20a%20trap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20US%20homeowners%20have%20loans%20that%20guarantee%20they'll%20pay%20the%20same%20amount%20each%20month%20for%20decades%2C%20regardless%20of%20inflation%20or%20the%20shifting%20winds%20of%20the%20economy.%20These%20are%20called%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20and%20they%20offer%20rare%20bright%20spots%20of%20certainty%20in%20the%20housing%20market's%20endless%20cycle%20of%20booms%20and%20busts.%20Lock%20in%20a%20favorable%20rate%2C%20and%20you're%20on%20the%20steady%20track%20to%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20sweetheart%20deals%20can%20cause%20big%20problems.%20When%20mortgage%20rates%20shoot%20up%2C%20as%20they%20did%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20many%20would-be%20sellers%20decide%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20move%20after%20all.%20Sure%2C%20a%20new%20home%20could%20be%20nice%2C%20but%20trading%20up%20would%20mean%20parting%20ways%20with%20a%20cheap%20mortgage%20rate.%20What%20may%20have%20been%20a%20welcome%20change%20suddenly%20sounds%20like%20a%20painful%2C%20expensive%20divorce.%20So%20they%20sit%20tight.%20A%20gummed-up%20housing%20market%20is%20good%20for%20nobody%3A%20First-time%20buyers%20can't%20find%20enough%20homes%20for%20sale%2C%20and%20wannabe%20sellers%20remain%20trapped%20in%20places%20that%20are%20either%20too%20big%20or%20too%20small.%20This%20is%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-mortgage-rates-outlook-home-prices-affordability-wealth-gap-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elock-in%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20linger%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20we've%20known%20about%20the%20lock-in%20possibility%20for%20many%2C%20many%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Campbell%2C%20a%20Harvard%20economist%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20didn't%20fix%20the%20roof%20while%20the%20sun%20was%20shining%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20raining.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20and%20housing%20wonks%20are%20obsessed%20with%20this%20uniquely%20American%20problem.%20One%20estimate%20suggests%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20prevented%20more%20than%201%20million%20people%20from%20selling%20their%20homes%20in%20the%20span%20of%20just%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20a%20steep%20toll%20considering%20about%205%20million%20homes%20exchange%20hands%20in%20a%20typical%20year.%20I%20used%20to%20think%20of%20these%20golden%20handcuffs%20as%20an%20inevitable%20side%20effect%20of%20the%20magical%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage.%20But%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20this%20way.%20The%20answer%20to%20our%20problems%20may%20lie%20thousands%20of%20miles%20away%20%E2%80%A6%20in%20Denmark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20homeowners%20in%20Denmark%2C%20like%20their%20American%20counterparts%2C%20enjoy%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages.%20But%20thanks%20to%20a%20quirk%20of%20their%20housing-finance%20system%2C%20Danish%20sellers%20are%20able%20to%20earn%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprofit%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhen%20they%20trade%20in%20their%20low%20mortgage%20rates%20for%20more-expensive%20ones%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20move%20even%20when%20rates%20rise.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Danes%20dodge%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImplementing%20a%20similar%20system%20in%20the%20US%20would%20require%20an%20overhaul%20of%20our%20mortgage%20market%20and%20would%20almost%20surely%20be%20met%20with%20lots%20of%20foot-dragging%20from%20regulators%20and%20investors.%20But%20the%20alternative%20%E2%80%94%20twiddling%20our%20thumbs%20until%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enext%20Housing%20Ice%20Age%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20far%20worse.%20Maybe%20it's%20time%20we%20take%20a%20page%20out%20of%20the%20Scandinavian%20playbook%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20may%20remember%20the%20pandemic-era%20housing%20market%20for%20its%20worst%20qualities%3A%20the%20bidding%20wars%2C%20the%20late-night%20doomscrolling%20on%20Zillow%2C%20the%20smug%20investors%20bragging%20on%20TikTok%20about%20how%20many%20homes%20they%20flipped%20that%20month.%20But%20regular%20house%20hunters%20scored%20a%20pretty%20good%20deal%20in%20at%20least%20one%20respect%3A%20Home%20loans%20were%20outrageously%20cheap.%20The%20typical%2030-year%20mortgage%20rate%20plummeted%20to%20a%20record%20low%20of%20about%202.65%25%20in%20late%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac.%20Existing%20homeowners%20pounced%20on%20the%20opportunity%2C%20too%2C%20refinancing%20their%20mortgages%20to%20get%20new%20loans%20with%20cheaper%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20began%20pushing%20up%20borrowing%20rates%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%20hoping%20to%20reel%20in%20rising%20inflation%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20went%20vertical.%20Rates%20doubled%20in%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20with%20the%20typical%20rate%20nearing%208%25%20in%20October%2C%20a%2020-year%20high.%20Rates%20have%20fallen%20a%20little%20since%20then%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20hovering%20at%20about%207%25.%20In%20the%20grand%20scheme%20of%20things%2C%20that's%20not%20crazy%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20buyers%20who%20bought%20homes%20in%20the%20early%20'80s%20may%20recall%20rates%20closer%20to%2018%25.%20But%20for%20buyers%20and%20homeowners%20who%20got%20used%20to%20rock-bottom%20rates%20in%20the%20decade%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20the%20reversal%20was%20chilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20working%20paper%20from%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency%20estimated%20that%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20prevented%201.3%20million%20home%20sales%20between%20mid-2022%20and%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20US%20mortgages%20have%20fixed%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20about%2096%25%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%2063%25%20of%20those%20had%20rates%20below%204%25.%20The%20agency%20estimated%20that%20with%20rates%20at%20about%207%25%2C%20these%20homeowners%20would%20pay%20roughly%20%24500%20more%20each%20month%20on%20their%20mortgage%20if%20they%20got%20a%20new%20rate%20on%20a%20house%20of%20the%20same%20value.%20If%20you%20do%20a%20little%20convoluted%20math%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20all%20those%20extra%20payments%20would%20be%20worth%20in%20today's%20dollars%2C%20it'd%20be%20like%20taking%20%2460%2C000%20and%20lighting%20it%20on%20fire%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FHFA's%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20rates%20were%20to%20fall%20to%206%25%20or%205.5%25%2C%20%26quot%3Byou're%20still%20going%20to%20have%20people%20who%20are%20not%20going%20to%20move%2C%20who%20are%20not%20going%20to%20give%20up%20their%20house%20forever%2C%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%20Will%20Doerner%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20FHFA%20and%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20paper%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20heck%20of%20a%20change%20for%20them%20to%20ever%20want%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20those%20mortgages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20so%20maybe%20you're%20not%20shedding%20any%20tears%20on%20behalf%20of%20these%20homeowners%20sitting%20on%20piles%20of%20equity%20and%20their%20sweet%2C%20sweet%20mortgage%20rates.%20But%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20warps%20the%20entire%20housing%20market.%20Fewer%20sellers%20means%20buyers%20compete%20for%20a%20smaller%20pool%20of%20available%20homes%2C%20driving%20up%20prices%20and%20locking%20out%20many%20first-time%20and%20low-income%20buyers.%20It%20means%20many%20people%20who%20want%20to%20move%20%E2%80%94%20to%20find%20a%20better%20job%2C%20start%20a%20family%2C%20upgrade%2C%20or%20downsize%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20have%20that%20option.%20A%20once%20theoretical%20hang-up%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20massive%20headache.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20golden%20shackles%20are%20a%20problem%20only%20in%20America.%20In%20Canada%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20or%20Australia%2C%20you%20can%20get%20a%20loan%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20for%20maybe%20five%20or%2010%20years%2C%20but%20then%20it'll%20adjust%20periodically%20to%20match%20the%20swings%20in%20the%20economy.%20Homeowners%20in%20these%20countries%20may%20not%20have%20to%20grapple%20with%20the%20same%20lock-in%20effect%2C%20but%20their%20monthly%20budgets%20get%20hit%20when%20borrowing%20rates%20go%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20Denmark%2C%20the%20only%20other%20country%20in%20which%20similar%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%20are%20widely%20available%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Danish%20borrowers%20have%20them.%20And%20just%20as%20they%20have%20in%20the%20US%2C%20rates%20for%20those%20mortgages%20have%20risen%20sharply.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%202022%2C%20the%20typical%20rate%20for%20a%2030-year%20mortgage%20in%20Denmark%20climbed%20by%20roughly%204%20percentage%20points%2C%20the%20largest%20jump%20in%2040%20years.%20But%20Denmark's%20housing-finance%20system%20is%20almost%20perfectly%20designed%20to%20shield%20it%20from%20the%20lock-in%20effect.%20And%20it's%20all%20thanks%20to%20a%20bit%20of%20financial%20magic%20known%20as%20covered%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20wish%20these%20things%20had%20sexier%20names%2C%20because%20if%2030-year-fixed%20mortgages%20are%20gifts%20to%20homeowners%2C%20then%20covered%20bonds%20are%20straight-up%20miracles.%20Here's%20how%20they%20work%3A%20When%20a%20bank%20gives%20a%20mortgage%20to%20a%20homebuyer%2C%20it%20creates%20matching%20bonds%20that%20it%20sells%20to%20investors.%20The%20bank%20gets%20cash%20to%20extend%20more%20loans%2C%20and%20the%20owners%20of%20these%20covered%20bonds%20get%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20payments%20from%20the%20people%20paying%20back%20the%20mortgage.%20The%20value%20of%20the%20bonds%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20value%20of%20the%20underlying%20mortgages%2C%20rises%20and%20falls%20like%20any%20other%20asset%20traded%20in%20the%20financial%20markets.%20When%20borrowing%20rates%20for%20new%20mortgages%20go%20up%2C%20the%20value%20of%20bonds%20tied%20to%20older%2C%20cheaper%20mortgages%20goes%20%3Cem%3Edown%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20investors%20hungry%20for%20higher%20returns%2C%20a%20loan%20that%20pays%207%25%20interest%20is%20worth%20more%20than%20one%20that%20pays%20only%203%25.%20This%20does%20not%20mean%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20value%20of%20the%20actual%20house%20has%20dropped%3B%20even%20if%20bond%20investors%20aren't%20as%20keen%20on%20the%20underlying%20loan%2C%20there%20may%20be%20plenty%20of%20regular%20buyers%20who%20still%20want%20the%20house.%20So%20far%2C%20this%20system%20of%20pooling%20together%20mortgage%20bonds%20and%20selling%20them%20to%20investors%20is%20pretty%20close%20to%20the%20American%20way%20of%20doing%20things.%20The%20real%20magic%20happens%20later%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20to%20settle%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20US%20homeowners%20pay%20off%20their%20mortgages%2C%20they%20have%20only%20one%20option%3A%20pony%20up%20the%20amount%20left%20on%20the%20loan.%20But%20when%20Danish%20homeowners%20pay%20off%20their%20mortgages%2C%20they%20have%20two%20choices%3A%20pay%20back%20the%20balance%20of%20their%20home%20loan%2C%20same%20as%20Americans%2C%20or%20pay%20the%20%3Cem%3Emarket%20value%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20amount%20their%20covered%20bonds%20would%20trade%20for%20on%20the%20open%20market.%20If%20interest%20rates%20go%20up%20and%20the%20value%20of%20those%20bonds%20falls%20below%20the%20amount%20remaining%20on%20their%20loan%2C%20it%20becomes%20cheaper%20for%20the%20Danes%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20mortgages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20an%20example%20in%20dollars%3A%20Let's%20say%20the%20face%20value%20of%20a%20mortgage%2C%20or%20the%20amount%20a%20homeowner%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20it%2C%20is%20%24500%2C000.%20But%20then%20interest%20rates%20rise%20by%2C%20say%2C%204%20percentage%20points.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20this%20turn%20of%20events%20would%20trap%20many%20homeowners%20in%20their%20house%3B%20they%20would%20have%20to%20not%20only%20pay%20back%20the%20%24500%2C000%20but%20get%20a%20new%20mortgage%20with%20higher%20interest%20payments.%20In%20the%20Danish%20model%2C%20the%20same%20situation%20could%20work%20out%20in%20the%20homeowner's%20favor.%20That's%20because%20as%20general%20interest%20rates%20rise%2C%20the%20market%20value%20of%20the%20covered%20bonds%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20underlying%20mortgage%2C%20drops.%20So%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20entire%20mortgage%2C%20the%20Danish%20homeowner%20could%20go%20out%20and%20buy%20back%20matching%20bonds%20for%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20%24400%2C000.%20If%20they%20sell%20their%20home%20for%20%24700%2C000%2C%20they%20get%20to%20pocket%20%24300%2C000%20instead%20of%20only%20%24200%2C000%20(not%20including%20pesky%20fees%2C%20of%20course).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20lucky%20Danish%20homeowner%20may%20have%20to%20turn%20around%20and%20buy%20another%20home%20with%20a%20higher%20rate%2C%20sure%2C%20but%20the%20profit%20from%20paying%20back%20their%20loan%20at%20its%20market%20value%20gives%20them%20a%20buffer%20to%20do%20so.%20Danes%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20sell%20their%20house%20to%20unlock%20their%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20choose%20to%20refinance.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20they%20would%20have%20to%20borrow%20only%20%24400%2C000%20instead%20of%20%24500%2C000%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20original%20loan.%20Again%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%20on%20the%20new%20loan%20is%20higher%2C%20but%20the%20principal%20balance%20is%20lower%2C%20so%20the%20monthly%20payments%20would%20stay%20roughly%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20Danes%20reap%20all%20the%20rewards%20when%20rates%20go%20up%20and%20face%20none%20of%20the%20downside%20risks%20when%20rates%20fall.%20Their%20mortgages%20are%20also%20assumable%2C%20which%20means%20sellers%20can%20hand%20off%20their%20loans%20to%20qualifying%20buyers.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Danish%20homeowners%20don't%20cling%20to%20their%20low-rate%20mortgages%20the%20way%20Americans%20do.%20Their%20setup%20%26quot%3Beliminates%20the%20lock-in%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Danish%20system%20may%20seem%20complex%2C%20it's%20not%20totally%20absurd%20to%20think%20we%20could%20adopt%20something%20similar%20here.%20It%20would%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20work%3A%20overhauls%20of%20Fannie%20Mae%20and%20Freddie%20Mac%2C%20a%20massive%20education%20campaign%20for%20consumers%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20an%20act%20of%20Congress.%20It's%20not%20as%20if%20you%20can%20just%20wave%20a%20wand%20and%20grant%20homeowners%20permission%20to%20start%20paying%20back%20their%20mortgages%20at%20market%20value%20%E2%80%94%20the%20existing%20contracts%20explicitly%20lay%20out%20the%20repayment%20terms%2C%20and%20mortgage%20bonds%20are%20bundled%20together%20here%20in%20a%20way%20that%20makes%20it%20impossible%20to%20pluck%20one%20out%20of%20the%20pool%20as%20they%20do%20in%20Denmark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnything%20that%20gives%20consumers%20protection%20from%20rising%20interest%20rates%20would%20come%20at%20a%20cost%2C%20too.%20Banks%20would%20demand%20borrowers%20pay%20higher%20interest%20rates%20from%20the%20start%20of%20their%20loans%2C%20Jesper%20Berg%2C%20the%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Danish%20Financial%20Supervisory%20Authority%2C%20told%20me.%20Danish%20mortgage%20rules%20are%20stricter%20in%20other%20ways%20that%20favor%20the%20lender%3A%20Borrowers%20are%20required%20to%20put%20down%2020%25%20of%20the%20home's%20price%2C%20and%20foreclosures%20are%20speedy%20thanks%20to%20a%20more%20creditor-friendly%20legal%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20still%20a%20way%20forward.%20There%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20some%20precedent%20for%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20mortgages%20%E2%80%94%20think%20back%20to%20the%20financial%20crisis%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%2C%20when%20the%20government%20instituted%20massive%20programs%20like%20HARP%20to%20help%20underwater%20homeowners%20refinance%20their%20mortgages.%20It%20required%20investor%20buy-in%20and%20lots%20of%20rule%20changes%20to%20rework%20existing%20loan%20terms%2C%20but%20it%20showed%20a%20willingness%20to%20adapt%20in%20dire%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECampbell%20isn't%20some%20starry-eyed%20dreamer%20who%20thinks%20we%20can%20snuff%20out%20these%20issues%20overnight.%20Embracing%20the%20Danish%20approach%20to%20mortgages%20would%20require%20much%20bigger%20changes%20than%20the%20recession-era%20programs%2C%20and%20mortgage%20reform%20tends%20to%20move%20at%20a%20glacial%20pace.%20But%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20intractable%20problem%20that%20demands%20big%20solutions.%20The%20Danish%20model%20combines%20the%20best%20of%20the%20US%20mortgage%20market%20%E2%80%94%20the%20stability%2C%20the%20cost%20savings%20for%20homeowners%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0with%20consumer%20protections%20to%20ensure%20they're%20not%20held%20hostage%20by%20those%20same%20perks.%20The%20Danes%20can%20move%20around%20during%20times%20when%20it%20would%20make%20little%20financial%20sense%20for%20US%20borrowers%20to%20do%20so.%20That's%20not%20just%20good%20for%20buyers%20or%20sellers%20or%20mortgage%20loan%20officers%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20good%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20it's%20a%20more%20efficient%20system%20that%20will%20prevent%20problems%20for%20both%20individual%20borrowers%20who%20get%20stuck%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20for%20the%20economy%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20which%20suffers%20when%20people%20get%20locked%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-mortgage-rates-lock-in-effect-home-buying-selling-easier-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716974821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66561a93a961b37edf3a6ebc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-mortgage-rates-lock-in-effect-home-buying-selling-easier-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20cruel%20twist%2C%20millions%20of%20Americans%20are%20trapped%20in%20their%20homes%20by%20low%20mortgage%20rates.%20Denmark's%20housing%20market%20offers%20a%20tantalizing%20alternative.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-mortgage-rates-lock-in-effect-home-buying-selling-easier-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anupam%20Kher%20recalls%20his%20acting%20debut%22%2C%22content%2