%20401(k)%20plan.%20But%20after%20about%20a%20year%20of%20%26quot%3Bchastising%26quot%3B%20from%20one%20of%20her%20supervisors%2C%20she%20said%20she%20finally%20gave%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20harping%20significantly%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20my%20life%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20Bell%20said%20she's%20meticulously%20tracked%20her%20budget%20and%20focused%20on%20saving.%20She%20now%20has%20roughly%20%24280%2C000%20in%20savings%20and%20retirement%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20way%20ahead%20of%20many%20of%20her%20peers%2C%20but%20it%20might%20not%20be%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20would%20like%20to%20retire%20around%20age%2065%20but%20isn't%20sure%20this%20will%20be%20possible.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUsing%20the%20NerdWallet%20retirement%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nerdwallet.com%2Fcalculator%2Fretirement-calculator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalculator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20estimated%20she'd%20need%20several%20million%20dollars%20in%20savings%20to%20retire%20comfortably.%20Assuming%20a%204%25%20annual%20investment%20return%20on%20her%20%24280%2C000%20savings%2C%20she'd%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Finvesting%2Finvestment-calculator%23B3KMByOEYe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%3C%2Fa%3E%20%24900%2C000%20in%2030%20years%2C%20her%20target%20retirement%20date.%20She'd%20have%20to%20invest%20an%20additional%20%2440%2C000%20each%20year%20to%20get%20to%20%243%20million%20in%20savings%20by%20age%2065.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20she%20put%20into%20the%20calculator%20that%20she'd%20need%2080%25%20of%20her%20annual%20pre-retirement%20income%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20six%20figures%20%E2%80%94%20to%20maintain%20her%20lifestyle%20in%20retirement.%20But%20when%20the%20calculator%20spit%20out%20a%20savings%20goal%20of%20over%20%246%20million%20%E2%80%94%20which%20felt%20impossible%20%E2%80%94%20she%20tried%2040%25%20instead.%20This%20provided%20a%20%243%20million%20savings%20goal%2C%20which%20she%20said%20still%20felt%20out%20of%20reach%2C%20but%20is%20a%20more%20realistic%20goal%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIdeally%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20overshoot%20the%20target%20and%20actually%20have%20something%20to%20pass%20down%20to%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20depressing%20to%20think%20I%20might%20not%20even%20be%20able%20to%20save%20enough%20for%20myself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFidelity%20recommends%20that%20people%20plan%20to%20need%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fidelity.com%2Fviewpoints%2Fretirement%2Fspending-in-retirement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E55%25%20and%2080%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20annual%20pre-retirement%20income%20to%20fund%20a%20retirement%20lifestyle%20they're%20satisfied%20with%2C%20though%20it%20depends%20on%20one's%20personal%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20saving%20for%20retirement%20can%20be%20a%20challenge%2C%20developing%20retirement%20savings%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20and%20figuring%20out%20if%20they're%20realistic%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20crucial%20yet%20complicated%20part%20of%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20suggestion%20that%20people%20should%20have%20saved%20100%25%20of%20their%20salary%20by%20age%2030%2C%20has%20many%20issues%2C%20experts%20say.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20that%20people%20don't%20always%20start%20working%20at%20the%20same%20point%20in%20their%2020s%2C%20said%20Chris%20Chen%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%20and%20cofounder%20of%20financial%20advisory%20firm%20Insight%20Financial%20Strategists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20when%20kids%20graduate%20from%20college%2C%20not%20very%20long%20thereafter%2C%20there%20might%20be%20graduate%20school%2C%20and%20that's%20going%20to%20put%20a%20dent%20in%20their%20style%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20these%20people%2C%20getting%20to%20the%20level%20of%20one-times%20earnings%20can%20be%20very%20difficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20he%20said%2C%20salaries%20for%20those%20who%20don't%20go%20to%20graduate%20school%20often%20won't%20be%20as%20high%20as%20those%20who%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20problem%20with%20the%20rule%20is%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20varies%20greatly%20depending%20on%20where%20one%20lives%2C%20says%20Judi%20Leahy%2C%20senior%20wealth%20advisor%20for%20Citi%20Personal%20Wealth%20Management.%20In%20big%20cities%2C%20costs%20are%20going%20to%20be%20much%20higher%2C%20but%20this%20is%20where%20job%20opportunities%20for%20some%20industries%20are%20concentrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20living%20in%20New%20York%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20harder%20to%20save%20money%20than%20if%20you're%20in%20Montana%2C%26quot%3B%20Leahy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20financial%20advisors%20say%20you%20should%20have%20savings%20that%20equal%20your%20salary%20at%2030%2C%20they%20recommend%20that%20people%20have%20three%20times%20their%20annual%20salary%20saved%20by%2040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20still%20difficult%2C%20this%20one%20should%20be%20easier%20to%20achieve%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20law%20of%20compound%20interest%20on%20previous%20savings%2C%20Chen%20said.%20When%20one%20is%20invested%20in%20securities%20like%20a%20bond%20or%20dividend-paying%20stock%2C%20they%20can%20choose%20to%20reinvest%20the%20yields%20they%20earn.%20Doing%20this%20repeatedly%20then%20snowballs%20the%20total%20return%20for%20the%20investor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20speaking%20with%20a%20financial%20advisor%2C%20some%20free%20online%20retirement%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20like%20those%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestor.vanguard.com%2Ftools-calculators%2Fretirement-income-calculator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Fretirement%2Fretirement-plan-calculator%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankrate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20NerdWallet%20%E2%80%94%20may%20be%20able%20to%20help%20people%20develop%20more%20personalized%20retirement%20goals%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eexperts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20tools%20aren't%20without%20their%20limitations.%20Bell%20%E2%80%94%20who%20used%20one%20of%20those%20calculators%20%E2%80%94%20said%20her%20future%20is%20too%20uncertain%20to%20accurately%20assess%20her%20retirement%20needs.%20For%20instance%2C%20Bell%20doesn't%20know%20where%20she'll%20be%20living%20when%20she%20retires%20and%20if%20that%20home%20will%20be%20paid%20off.%20What's%20more%2C%20she%20can't%20anticipate%20what%20health%20needs%20she'll%20have%20when%20she%20stops%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20I'll%20be%20at%20that%20point%20in%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20it%20seems%20almost%20impossible%20to%20guess%20what%20is%20really%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20many%20millennials%20may%20feel%20similar%20to%20Bell%3A%20It%20can%20seem%20impossible%20to%20predict%20how%20much%20you'll%20need%20for%20possibly%2020%20or%2030%20years%20of%20your%20life%20without%20an%20annual%20salary.%20Even%20if%20someone%20saves%20what%20they%20think%20is%20enough%2C%20there's%20no%20telling%20exactly%20how%20much%20they'll%20need%20for%20any%20family%20emergencies%20or%20health%20crises%20that%20arise.%20If%20it%20turns%20out%20they%20haven't%20saved%20enough%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20social%20safety%20net%20in%20the%20US%20means%20they%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20work%20well%20past%20their%20desired%20retirement%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20millennials%20can%20get%20their%20retirement%20savings%20back%20on%20track%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20millennials%20are%20struggling%20financially%2C%20it's%20not%20all%20doom%20and%20gloom%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20their%20retirement%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Vanguard%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstitutional.vanguard.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Finst%2Fiig-transformation%2Finsights%2Fpdf%2F2023%2Fthe-vanguard-retirement-outlook.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20October%20found%20that%20early%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2037%20and%2041%20%E2%80%94%20were%20better%20positioned%20for%20retirement%20than%20older%20generations.%20Vanguard%20attributed%20this%20in%20part%20to%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-oks-big-changes-to-how-americans-save-for-retirement-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPension%20Protection%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202006%2C%20which%20it%20found%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20Americans%20to%20join%20their%20workplace%20retirement%20plans%20and%20increase%20their%20savings%20rates%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Fidelity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpreview.thenewsmarket.com%2FPreviews%2FFINP%2FDocumentAssets%2F663841.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20last%20December%20%E2%80%94%20in%20partnership%20with%20consumer%20research%20firm%20Big%20Village%20%E2%80%94%20of%20more%20than%202%2C000%20US%20adults%20with%20an%20investment%20account%2C%2075%25%20of%20millennials%20surveyed%20said%20they%20were%20confident%20they'd%20be%20able%20to%20retire%20when%20and%20how%20they%20want.%20The%20survey%20found%20that%20millennials%20started%20saving%20for%20retirement%20earlier%20than%20both%20Gen%20X%20and%20boomers.%20What's%20more%2C%20Fidelity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.fidelity.com%2Fpressreleases%2Ffidelity-research--america-s-retirement-preparedness-level-declines-amid-continued-volatility%2Fs%2Fc57ac0e9-9c5c-4f5c-938c-cdf82a3aa7b1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20year%20found%20that%2C%20since%202020%2C%20millennials%20have%20seen%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-wealth-balloon-pandemic-stimulus-savings-investing-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarger%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20median%20income%20than%20any%20other%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20for%20the%20other%20millennials%20who%20are%20behind%20on%20their%20retirement%20savings%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20tricks%20that%20can%20make%20up%20for%20lost%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20start%20saving%20whatever%20you%20can%2C%20when%20you%20can.%20Nilay%20Gandhi%2C%20CFP%20senior%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Vanguard%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20recommends%20people%20put%20between%2010%25%20and%2015%25%20of%20their%20annual%20pre-tax%20income%20toward%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20are%20putting%20money%20into%20a%20retirement%20account%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fira-vs-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%20or%20a%20Roth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20offers%20diversified%20investments%20and%20tax%20advantages%20%E2%80%94%20and%20getting%20any%20deposit%20matches%20that%20your%20company%20might%20offer.%20Many%20firms%20match%20deposits%20up%20to%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20an%20employee's%20salary.%20The%20maximum%20one%20can%20contribute%20to%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20which%20is%20funded%20by%20post-tax%20deposits%2C%20is%20%247%2C000%20in%202024.%20For%20a%20401(k)%2C%20which%20is%20for%20pre-tax%20deposits%2C%20the%20maximum%20this%20year%20is%20%2423%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20should%20religiously%20put%20their%20money%20in%20there%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20Roth%20version%20or%20the%20traditional%20version%2C%20and%20at%20the%20very%20least%20pick%20up%20the%20match%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20if%20you%20have%20an%20investment%20portfolio%2C%20make%20sure%20it%20has%20the%20right%20mix%20of%20stocks%2C%20bonds%2C%20and%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeahy%20said%20that%20those%20in%20their%2030s%20may%20want%20to%20think%20about%20leaning%20more%20heavily%20into%20stocks%20given%20their%20longer%20investing%20timeline%20and%20higher%20risk%20tolerance.%20Older%20investors%20may%20want%20to%20consider%20higher%20allocations%20to%20safer%20options%20like%20fixed-income%20assets%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20trying%20to%20play%20catch%20up%20at%2045%20or%2055%20and%20you%20think%20you%20want%20to%20go%20all%20in%20on%20equities%2C%20it%20might%20not%20be%20your%20best%20bet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concern%20for%20some%20millennials%20isn't%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20money%20to%20put%20toward%20retirement%20savings%2C%20it's%20that%20they're%20investing%20it%20too%20conservatively%2C%20Rita%20Assaf%2C%20vice%20president%2C%20retirement%20savings%20at%20Fidelity%20Investments%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAssaf%20said%20Fidelity's%20research%20found%20that%20millennials%20have%20seen%20the%20largest%20drop%20in%20%26quot%3Bage-appropriate%20asset%20allocation%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20they're%20holding%20too%20much%20of%20their%20savings%20in%20cash%20and%20bonds%20than%20she%20would%20typically%20recommend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EThese%20indicators%20point%20toward%20a%20trend%20of%20millennials%20taking%20a%20more%20conservative%20approach%20to%20investing%2C%20which%20likely%20stems%20from%20the%20fact%20they%20have%20multiple%20other%20savings%20priorities%20of%20their%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20concern%20is%20that%20millennials%20may%20not%20end%20up%20with%20the%20appropriate%20mix%20of%20assets%20to%20help%20them%20adequately%20achieve%20their%20retirement%20goals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20solid%20investment%20strategy%20is%20important%2C%20allocating%20more%20money%20toward%20saving%20is%20the%20most%20important%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20an%20individual%20is%20not%20saving%20enough%2C%20even%20the%20best%20investment%20strategy%20is%20unlikely%20to%20help%20them%20reach%20their%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20Gandhi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESavings%20outside%20a%20retirement%20account%20are%20also%20important%2C%20Chen%20said%2C%20and%20one%20should%20start%20by%20building%20up%20at%20least%20six%20months%20of%20expenses%20for%20an%20emergency%20fund.%20One%20way%20to%20do%20this%20is%20to%20have%20money%20deposited%20directly%20from%20their%20paycheck%20into%20a%20separate%20account.%20And%20with%20certificates%20of%20deposit%20paying%20annualized%20rates%20around%205%25%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20Leahy%20said%20savers%20are%20even%20more%20incentivized%20to%20hold%20onto%20their%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Leahy%20and%20Chen%20also%20agreed%20that%20credit%20card%20use%20should%20be%20avoided%20for%20those%20who%20are%20not%20highly%20confident%20that%20they%20can%20pay%20off%20their%20balance%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20not%20maintain%20a%20credit%20card%20balance.%20That's%20a%20great%20way%20to%20erode%20capital%20because%20the%20card%20is%20charging%20you%20anywhere%20from%2012%25%20to%2022%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Leahy%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that%20item%20that%20you%20bought%20that%20was%20on%20sale%20that%20you%20really%20didn't%20need%20wasn't%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20some%20millennials%2C%20following%20most%20of%20this%20advice%20might%20not%20be%20enough%20for%20them%20to%20reach%20their%20retirement%20goals.%20It%20could%20force%20them%20to%20join%20the%20millions%20of%20Americans%20working%20well%20into%20their%20sixties%20and%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20started%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20possibility%20that%20she%20might%20have%20to%20work%20later%20in%20life%20than%20she%20initially%20hoped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20fortunate%20to%20be%20in%20an%20industry%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20work%20well%20past%20retirement%20age%20because%20it's%20not%20very%20physically%20intensive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Hudson-Hartman%20said%20he%20takes%20comfort%20from%20the%20fact%20he%20enjoys%20working%20%E2%80%94%20and%20has%20an%20income%20stream%20he%20can%20count%20on%20well%20past%20age%2070%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20planned%20to%20do%20gig%20work%20part-time%20in%20my%20later%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20plan%20to%20just%20dial%20it%20back%20and%20work%20during%20busy%20times%20and%20keep%20my%20mornings%20and%20afternoons%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20millennial%20willing%20to%20talk%20about%20your%20retirement%20savings%20journey%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Awedwards%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ewedwards%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-millennials-need-for-retirement-savings-strategies-401k-ira-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716972962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6626d5c50dfb1341e9fdcd17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-millennials-need-for-retirement-savings-strategies-401k-ira-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Feel%20like%20you're%20behind%20on%20retirement%20savings%3F%20You're%20not%20alone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20